After thinking about this a bit, I believe that this should give you what you want:

```
package org.antlr.v4.runtime;

import org.antlr.v4.runtime.TokenStream;
import org.antlr.v4.runtime.TokenStreamRewriter;

public class MyTokenStreamRewriter extends TokenStreamRewriter {
    public MyTokenStreamRewriter(TokenStream tokens) {
        super(tokens);
    }

    public int getRewriteCount() {
        return getRewriteCount(DEFAULT_PROGRAM_NAME);
    }

    public int getRewriteCount(String programName) {
        return programs.get(programName).size();
    }
}
```

Then, instead of `TokenStreamRewriter`, create a `MyTokenStreamRewriter` (or whatever you wish to call it).  You really want to know how many rewrites are scheduled for a given program or the default program (not really a tokenIndex).

